---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import CtaSection from '../components/CtaSection.astro';

const title = 'The Method | Nascent Strategy';
const description =
  'We help businesses find the clarity already inside them, then build what makes it useful. Kansas City, built for anywhere.';

const phases = [
  {
    id: 'see',
    num: '01',
    name: 'SEE',
    headline: 'We start with the instinct, not the technology.',
    body: 'Most owners can feel where the opportunity is before they can prove it. Our first job is to take that instinct seriously, then go looking for what supports it. Sometimes the answer is in your own data: who’s leaving, who’s staying, what your best customers have in common, where the margin slips. Sometimes it’s in a workflow that costs more than anyone realizes, because the team has adapted around it. And sometimes it’s in your market, which is where we bring our own data to add a view your records can’t. We look before we conclude.',
    output: 'Output begins here: a clear read on where the opportunity actually is.',
  },
  {
    id: 'solve',
    num: '02',
    name: 'SOLVE',
    headline: 'People ask for the thing they can name. Not always the thing they need.',
    body: 'A client asks for a dashboard when the real problem is that no one agrees on which numbers matter. Someone asks for an automation when the process itself is the issue. This is why strategy comes first. We take what the seeing surfaced and turn it into a decision: what’s worth pursuing, what it’s worth in dollars or hours, and what it would take to get there. Strategy gives the build a reason to exist. Skip it and you just make the wrong thing faster.',
    output: 'Output: a ranked picture of the opportunities, costed and ordered by what pays back first.',
  },
  {
    id: 'build',
    num: '03',
    name: 'BUILD',
    headline: 'The answer has to live where the work happens.',
    body: 'What we build takes one of two shapes, depending on what we found. When the opportunity is something you couldn’t see, we build the view: a way to read the signal in your data and your market, in plain enough form that your team can act on it. When the opportunity is buried in friction, we build the tool that removes it, the software that makes the better way the easier way. Either one gets installed where your team already works, measured against the baseline we set, and looked after over time. Embedded systems are living systems.',
    output: 'Output: a working system, a measurement plan, and a standing optimization retainer.',
  },
];
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <!-- MTH-01 Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow reveal">The Method</span>
      <h1 class="reveal">See it. Solve it. Build it.</h1>
      <p class="lede page-hero-sub reveal">
        We&rsquo;re known for the seeing and trusted for the building. Strategy
        that doesn&rsquo;t stop at a deck, and software that doesn&rsquo;t start
        until we understand the question. It works in any business, because
        every business has clarity it hasn&rsquo;t reached yet.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MTH-02 through MTH-04: pinned sequence on desktop, stacked below 1024px -->
  <section class="phases" id="phases">
    <div class="phases-track" id="phases-track">
      <div class="wrap phases-frame">
        <div class="phase-rail" aria-hidden="true">
          <span class="phase-rail-tick mono" id="phase-tick">01</span>
          <span class="phase-rail-line"><span class="phase-rail-fill" id="phase-fill"></span></span>
        </div>

        <div class="phase-panels" id="phase-panels">
          {phases.map((p, i) => (
            <article class="phase-panel stagger" id={p.id} data-index={i}>
              <p class="phase-label mono reveal">{p.num} / {p.name}</p>
              <h2 class="phase-headline reveal">{p.headline}</h2>
              <p class="phase-body reveal">{p.body}</p>
              <p class="phase-output mono reveal">{p.output}</p>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MTH-05 Measurement promise -->
  <section class="section measure on-ink">
    <div class="wrap grid measure-grid">
      <div class="measure-copy">
        <span class="eyebrow reveal">How We Keep Score</span>
        <h2 class="reveal">Baseline first. Build&nbsp;second.</h2>
        <p class="measure-body reveal">
          Before anything ships, we record where the number stands today: the
          revenue, the hours, the rate, whatever the opportunity was worth.
          After it ships, we measure what moved. That&rsquo;s the whole
          discipline. It keeps us honest, it keeps the retainer earning its
          place, and it means you never have to take our word for anything.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="measure-metric reveal">
        <!-- [PLACEHOLDER] Sample metric figure, founder to confirm -->
        <p class="metric-figure mono figure-ember" data-countup="184000" data-prefix="$">$184,000</p>
        <p class="metric-caption mono">The only language we report in.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MTH-06 Stack explanation -->
  <section class="section stack">
    <div class="wrap grid stack-grid">
      <div class="stack-lead">
        <span class="eyebrow reveal">What &ldquo;AI&rdquo; Means Here</span>
        <h2 class="reveal">One platform, used deliberately.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="stack-body reveal">
        <p>
          AI is not automatically useful. It becomes useful when it&rsquo;s
          pointed at the right question, connected to the right data, and
          placed inside a workflow people will actually use. We build on
          Anthropic&rsquo;s Claude platform, in two layers. One lives where
          your team works: a secure workspace with custom skills and
          connections to your tools. The other is custom software built on the
          Claude API, for the views and tools that run your specific fix. Your
          data stays yours, in systems you control.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MTH-07 Closing CTA -->
  <CtaSection
    headline="It starts with a four-week assessment."
    ctaLabel="See the assessment"
    ctaHref="/assessment"
  />
</Base>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding-top: calc(var(--section-pad) * 1.1);
    padding-bottom: var(--section-pad);
  }
  .page-hero h1 { max-width: 14ch; margin-top: 0; }
  .page-hero-sub { margin-top: 1.75rem; max-width: 52ch; }

  /* Phases: stacked by default (mobile, no-JS); JS pins on >=1024px */
  .phases { border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline); }
  .phases-frame {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 72px minmax(0, 1fr);
    column-gap: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 4rem);
  }
  .phase-rail { display: none; }

  .phase-panel {
    padding-block: calc(var(--section-pad) * 0.75);
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .phase-panel + .phase-panel { border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline); }

  .phase-label {
    font-size: var(--text-eyebrow);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-eyebrow);
    color: var(--signal);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .phase-headline { font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); max-width: 20ch; }
  .phase-body { margin-top: 1.5rem; color: var(--slate); max-width: 62ch; }
  .phase-output {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding: 1.125rem 1.375rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--signal);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink);
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  /* Desktop pinned layout, activated by JS via .is-pinned */
  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .phases-frame { grid-template-columns: 72px minmax(0, 1fr); }

    .phases.is-pinned .phases-track {
      height: 100vh;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .phases.is-pinned .phases-frame { width: 100%; }
    .phases.is-pinned .phase-rail {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 1.25rem;
      height: 60vh;
    }
    .phase-rail-tick {
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
      color: var(--signal);
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    }
    .phase-rail-line {
      position: relative;
      flex: 1;
      width: 1px;
      background: var(--hairline);
    }
    .phase-rail-fill {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background: var(--signal);
      transform-origin: top;
      transform: scaleY(0);
    }

    .phases.is-pinned .phase-panels {
      position: relative;
      display: grid;
    }
    .phases.is-pinned .phase-panel {
      grid-area: 1 / 1;
      border-top: 0;
      padding-block: 0;
    }
    .phases.is-pinned .phase-panel:not(.is-active) {
      opacity: 0;
      filter: blur(6px);
      pointer-events: none;
    }
  }

  /* MTH-05 */
  .measure-grid { row-gap: 3rem; align-items: center; }
  .measure-copy { grid-column: 1 / span 6; }
  .measure-body { margin-top: 1.5rem; color: var(--slate-on-ink); }
  .measure-metric {
    grid-column: 8 / -1;
    border-left: 1px solid var(--hairline-on-ink);
    padding-left: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 3rem);
  }
  .metric-figure {
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .metric-caption {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--slate-on-ink);
  }

  /* MTH-06 */
  .stack-grid { row-gap: 2rem; }
  .stack-lead { grid-column: 1 / span 5; }
  .stack-body { grid-column: 7 / -1; color: var(--slate); align-self: end; }

  @media (max-width: 1023px) {
    .phases-frame { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .measure-copy, .measure-metric, .stack-lead, .stack-body { grid-column: 1 / -1; }
    .measure-metric { border-left: 0; padding-left: 0; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  import '../scripts/method.js';
</script>
